cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 175 miles SW of Fort Myers, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: Moving north-northeast, expected to strike the west-central Florida coast Thursday, cross north-central Florida, then turn northeast and pass near the Georgia–South Carolina coast before weakening inland.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: west-central coast of Florida between Anna Maria Island and Yankeetown

weather_observation.watch_coast: Hurricane Watch Anna Maria Island to Yankeetown FL; Tropical Storm Watch north of Suwannee River to Aucilla River FL and portions of western Cuba
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning Dry Tortugas and Bonita Beach to Suwannee River FL
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Gulf Coast of Florida, Big Bend, then Atlantic coasts of northeastern Florida, Georgia, and South Carolina
weather_observation.wind: Occasional tropical-storm-force gusts (to 40 mph) possible Friday as Eta passes offshore.
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along the Georgia coast given track and weakening, though minor tidal rises are possible.
weather_observation.rainfall: 1–3 inches of rain with locally higher amounts possible Friday into Saturday, leading to brief ponding and minor river rises.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Isolated tornadoes in outer rainbands and dangerous rip currents along adjacent beaches.
